Key Match Events: Simon Msuva scored an 11th-minute goal for Tanzania
Patson Daka scored an 88th-minute equalizer for Zambia
Pre-Game Insights: Tanzania had not won in their previous finals appearances in 1980 and 2019
Tanzania's coach Adel Amrouche was handed an eight-match suspension on Friday
Post-Match Reflections: Zambia managed to equalize despite trailing 1-0
Tanzania were denied a first win at the African Cup of Nations
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Stade Laurent Pokou in San-Pedro, Ivory Coast
